# Paco Prototype Rule

When working on this repository, treat the goal as building a complete Expo/React Native front-end prototype of Paco App with mock data.

Mandatory sources before coding:
- `AGENTS.md`
- `funcionalidadvideo.md`
- `assets/videosfuncioalidades/WhatsApp Video 2026-02-03 at 13.45.15.mp4`
- `assets/videosfuncioalidades/WhatsApp Video 2026-02-03 at 13.48.21.mp4`
- `docs/claude-fable/one-shot-master-prompt.md`
- `docs/claude-fable/functional-spec.md`
- `docs/claude-fable/acceptance-checklist.md`

Do not copy the reference app pixel-perfect. Use the videos to extract behavior, flows, edge cases, hierarchy and content. Rebuild with a modern corporate UX using the repo storybook/components as the design base.

No superficial coverage:
- A module is not done when it has only a card, route, static list or descriptive text.
- Every module needs navigable flows, mock data, local state, actions, feedback, empty/loading/error/success states where relevant, and cross-module effects when the reference implies them.
- Every visible primary button must do something observable.

Expo rule:
- Expo changed. Before using Expo/React Native APIs, consult exact SDK 56 docs at `https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v56.0.0/`.

Definition of done:
- `npm run typecheck` passes.
- No new lints in touched files.
- All items in `docs/claude-fable/acceptance-checklist.md` are implemented or explicitly marked as a visible mock limitation.
